g.aria-label: A type of bacteria called Agrobacterium causes a variety of plant diseases such as Crown Gall and Hairy Root that result in plant death and agricultural loss.
In Agrobacterium, the ability to infect a plant is contained in a gene on a plasmid that is transferred from one bacteria to another through a process called conjugation.
When they are transferred, the ability to infect plants is transmitted as well.
